oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Mr. Alexander's alfalfa field
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Clement, William L., photographer
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: O.B. Alexander is shown in field of alfalfa on class two land, seeded in the fall of 1963 and treated in accordance with recommendations based on soil test. Field treated with Heptachlora for weevil control. Located five miles west of Woodbury.

One in a series of photographs of agricultural activities in Cannon County, TN that were taken by W.L. Clement, District Conservationist for the U.S. Soil Conservation Service, and his assistants between the mid-1940s and mid-1970s.
